#Topic Canvas
#Class SkCanvas

Canvas provides an interface for drawing, and how the drawing is clipped and transformed.
Canvas contains a stack of Canvas_Matrix and Canvas_Clip values.

Canvas and Paint together provide the state to draw into Surface or Device.
Each Canvas draw call transforms the geometry of the object by the concatenation of all Canvas_Matrix
values in the stack. 
The transformed geometry is clipped by the intersection of all of Canvas_Clip values in the stack.
The Canvas draw calls take Paint parameter for drawing state.
Create Paint to supply the drawing state, such as Paint_Color,
Paint_Typeface, Paint_Text_Size, Stroke_Width, Paint_Shader and so on.

To draw to a pixel-based destination, create Raster_Surface or GPU_Surface. 
Request Canvas from Surface to obtain the interface to draw. 
Canvas generated by Raster_Surface draws to memory visible to the CPU. 
Canvas generated by GPU_Surface uses Vulcan or OpenGL to draw to the GPU.

Canvas can be constructed to draw to Bitmap without first creating Raster_Surface.
This approach may be deprecated in the future.  

To draw to a document, obtain Canvas from SVG_Canvas, PDF_Document, or Picture_Recorder.
Document-based Canvas and other Canvas subclasses reference Device describing the destination.

#Subtopic Canvas_Constructors

Create the desired type of Surface to obtain its Canvas when possible. Canvas_Constructors are useful
when no Surface is required, and some helpers implicitly create Raster_Surface.

